================================================================================
 SBI-style Deposit Calculator — Liferay 7.3 UI Fragment + Service Builder rates
 Reference scaffold — adapt module/package names to your workspace before use.
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
0. ARCHITECTURE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Rates live in a DB table owned by Service Builder. The fragment never talks to
Service Builder directly — it calls a REST Builder resource, because:
  - typed OpenAPI contract (fragment JS + any other consumer share one schema)
  - standard HTTP GET -> cacheable (ETag / Cache-Control), unlike jsonws
  - no reflection-based invocation, smaller attack surface than jsonws
  - versioned path (/v1.0/...) so the fragment doesn't break on service changes

  [deposit-calculator fragment]
          | fetch() GET /products once on load, GET /interest-rates once per
          | tenure/customer-type change (not per keystroke)
          v
  [deposit-rate-rest]  /o/deposit-rate/v1.0/{interest-rates,products}
          | InterestRateLocalServiceUtil.findByCustomerType_Product_Tenure(...)
          | DepositProductLocalServiceUtil.findByActive(true)
          v
  [deposit-rate-service]  InterestRate + DepositProduct entities (Service Builder)

Section 4 shows the lighter-weight alternative (@JSONWebService + Liferay.Service)
in case the extra REST module isn't worth it for your setup.

