5. FORMULA REFERENCE (from Annexure 4, verified against the worked example)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example: P=100000, r=8%, t=1 year, n=4 (quarterly)
  Maturity Amount = 100000 * (1 + 0.08/4)^4 = 108243.00 [matches example: 1,08,243]
  Total Interest (Accumulated) = 8243.00
  Quarterly Payout = 100000 * 0.08 / 4 = 2000.00/quarter [matches example]
  Monthly Payout ~= 8243 / 12 = 686.92 ~= 687/month [matches example]
  On Maturity Payout = TotalInterest in full

Annual Payout (tenure > 1yr) — true year-by-year compounding, not a flat
TotalInterest/tenureYears average, per the doc's own caveat that "compounding
within the year is still quarterly":
  Per-year payout = P * ((1 + r/4)^4 - 1)   [same figure repeats every full year,
                                              since the payout removes that
                                              year's interest and principal
                                              resets to P for the next year]
  e.g. P=100000, r=8%: 100000 * (1.02^4 - 1) = 8243.22/year
  Partial trailing year (if tenure isn't a whole number of years) is settled
  at maturity: remainder = P * ((1 + r/4)^(4 * fractionalYears) - 1)
